            rdf:value "An approach to soil management that excludes conventional tillage operations that invert the soil and bury crop residues. There are five types of conservation tillage systems: no-tillage (slot planting), mulch tillage, strip or zonal tillage, ridge tillage (including no-till on ridges) and reduced or minimum tillage."@en ] ;
