            rdf:value "Lithology refers to the physical characteristics of the parent material, such as the mineral composition, texture, and structure of the underlying rocks or sediments. The lithology of an area influences soil formation by affecting drainage, nutrient content, and the ability of the soil to support vegetation. Source: AGI, 'Encyclopedia of Geology'"@en ] ;
