    skos:definition [ dcterms:source agrovoc:c_b8039965 ;
            rdf:value "Termites are social insects that build large nests in soil or wood and can occasionally cause damage to wooden structures. They are sometimes called 'white ants', however they belong to a completely different insect group (Order Isoptera) to true ants (Order Hymenoptera)."@en ] ;
