            rdf:value "Phosphorus retention measures a soil's capacity to adsorb and hold phosphorus, influenced by soil texture, pH, and mineralogy. While high retention reduces leaching, it may also limit phosphorus availability to plants. Understanding phosphorus retention helps optimize fertilization and minimize environmental impacts. Source: Brady & Weil (2017)."@en ] ;
