eusoilvoc:CationExchangeCapacity a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader eusoilvoc:SoilChemicalCapacity ;
    skos:broaderTransitive eusoilvoc:SoilChemicalCapacity,
        eusoilvoc:SoilChemicalProperties,
        eusoilvoc:SoilProperties ;
    skos:definition [ dcterms:source agrovoc:c_24981 ;
            rdf:value "A measure of the soil’s ability to hold positively charged ions. The clay mineral and organic matter components of soil have negatively charged sites on their surfaces which adsorb and hold  positively charged ions (cations). This electrical charge is critical to the supply of nutrients to plants because many nutrients (e.g. Mg, K and Ca) exist as cations."@en ],
        [ dcterms:source glosis_lh:cationExchangeCapacityProperty ;
            rdf:value "The Cation Exchange Capacity (CEC) measures the soil's total capacity to hold and exchange positively charged ions (cations). It is influenced by clay and organic matter content and is a critical indicator of soil fertility and nutrient retention. Source: Brady, N.C., & Weil, R.R. (2008). The Nature and Properties of Soils."@en ] ;
    skos:exactMatch agrovoc:c_24981,
        spp:CationExchangeCapacity,
        glosis_lh:cationExchangeCapacityProperty,
        she:CationExchangeCapacity ;
    skos:inScheme <https://w3id.org/eusoilvoc> ;
    skos:narrower eusoilvoc:CationExchangeCapacityEffective,
        eusoilvoc:CationExchangeCapacitySoil,
        eusoilvoc:EffectiveCEC ;
    skos:narrowerTransitive eusoilvoc:CationExchangeCapacityEffective,
        eusoilvoc:CationExchangeCapacitySoil,
        eusoilvoc:EffectiveCEC ;
    skos:prefLabel "cation exchange capacity"@en ;
    eusoilvoc:skosmosHierarchyParent eusoilvoc:SoilChemicalCapacity .

