            rdf:value "Total carbon in soil includes both organic carbon (from plant and microbial residues) and inorganic carbon (primarily carbonates). It is a fundamental component of soil organic matter, influencing soil fertility, structure, and water retention. High carbon levels are associated with better soil health and productivity. Source: USDA NRCS."@en ] ;
